text: The Boholano is a variant dialect of Standard Cebuano spoken fluently in Bohol province, mostly Boholanos in some parts of western Bohol including Tagbilaran using the Cebuano language, it has a different in terms of words and its grammar.https://micolle.wordpress.com/2011/05/20/bol-anon-dialecthttps://en- academic.com/dic.nsf/enwiki/883407 ==References== Category:Dialects of the Philippines
